        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Build a flat, linear document structure where all lines are direct children of an empty root node — the simplest possible document representation. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Flat structure construction, TreeNode assembly, metadata propagation. \par \b Input\/ \:  UnstructuredDocument (lines + tables + metadata). \par \b Output\/ \:  ParsedDocument with a flat line tree. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(8): AbstractStructureConstructor, TreeNode, DocumentContent, DocumentMetadata] \par \b Links to Spec\/ \:  REQ-STR-003: A linear (flat) structure must be available as the simplest document representation. \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Root node ALWAYS has the empty lines list.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>All document lines become direct children of the root.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Metadata is copied from the UnstructuredDocument. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why an empty root node instead of making the first line the root? A: A uniform root with empty lines ensures all constructors produce the same TreeNode shape, simplifying downstream consumers. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Semantic template markup and LDD logging added] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 8[Flat linear structure constructor] =&gt; LinearConstructor METHOD 9[Assemble flat document tree from lines] =&gt; construct \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[construct]: StructureExtractor → AssembleFlatTree → ProduceLinearParsedDocument </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
